Now here's another idea which when it came out I actually thought was pretty neat.

01:33.270 --> 01:34.680
It's called Fish on wheels.

01:34.860 --> 01:39.420
And essentially it's a fish tank where your pet goldfish can swim.

01:39.570 --> 01:46.230
And if they swim to the front of the fish tank the fish tank is also attached to wheels which will move

01:46.230 --> 01:47.550
the fish forwards.

01:47.640 --> 01:53.730
So the idea is that while you're gone your fish Sally might be able to navigate around the house and

01:53.730 --> 01:57.860
go wherever she likes by swimming in that direction.

01:57.870 --> 01:59.520
So I thought it was actually a neat idea.

01:59.520 --> 02:06.240
I'm not sure that anybody would ever need it but it was actually featured on Tech Crunch wired and a

02:06.240 --> 02:09.640
whole bunch of other big tech blogs.

02:09.690 --> 02:15.840
So you know it definitely had the traffic hitting it but unfortunately it just wasn't a good enough

02:15.840 --> 02:16.500
idea.

02:16.500 --> 02:21.390
It's one of those things that could have been really big like potato salad or grizzly coat but it just

02:21.390 --> 02:23.370
didn't capture people's imagination.

02:23.370 --> 02:27.060
So use this platform as an experiment.

02:27.060 --> 02:32.430
Use it as a testing base where you can see if your ideas get any traction.

